## ததஅக

[ kaṉmam ]  
  
s. பார். கருமம்  
action  
s. moral actions  
especially in their effectsas the cause of transmi grations and their accompanying joys and sorrows  
pleasure and pains  
intelligence or stupidity  
c.  
சஞ்சிதகன்மம்  
2. ac tions  
செய்தொழில்  
3. evil actions  
evil  
vice  
தீவினை. (பார். கருமம்.)  
4. fate  
destiny  
the fruits  
retributions  
of actions in former births  
பிராரத்தகன்மம். wils. p  
198. karmman. in the agamas  
actions and their effects are of three classes  
viz:  
1. ஆகாமியம்  
moral actions  
good and evil of the present life  
considered as the source of future births with their suffering and en joyment  
2. சஞ்சிதம்  
the accumulated actions of the soul in former births  
the retributions of which are to be experienced in future transmigrations  
3. பிராரத்தம் or பிராரத்துவம்  
the enjoyment and sufferings apportioned to the soul in the present state as the retributions of actions in former births. அவனைக்கொல்லாதேகன்மம்பிடிக்கும். do not kill him  
if you do  
the action will seize you  
